It was beautiful,
not to brag.

1041
01:06:32,492 --> 01:06:35,245
Tony sang a song that Sammy
wrote for the occasion called...

1042
01:06:35,329 --> 01:06:38,916
"The girl that I marry,
then married. "

1043
01:06:38,999 --> 01:06:42,169
The other girls, being single,
naturally cried at the wedding.

1044
01:06:42,252 --> 01:06:44,671
Somewhere else
in Hollywood...

1045
01:06:44,755 --> 01:06:47,257
someone was crying
more than anybody.

1046
01:06:52,721 --> 01:06:55,891
He's dead!
The man is dead.

1047
01:06:55,974 --> 01:06:58,268
I'll get pictures
of him dead.

1048
01:06:58,310 --> 01:07:02,272
You can pin 'em on your wall
and throw darts at them.

1049
01:07:02,314 --> 01:07:05,776
Last time, he tells us,
he got married at gunpoint.

1050
01:07:05,817 --> 01:07:09,112
What did they have this time?
A cannon?

1051
01:07:12,157 --> 01:07:14,034
Mr. Pearl?

1052
01:07:15,911 --> 01:07:20,123
We're almost done packing.
I'll call you to pick up the bags.

1053
01:07:20,207 --> 01:07:23,210
We got a going-away
gift for you...

1054
01:07:23,293 --> 01:07:25,963
from a friend.

1055
01:07:30,050 --> 01:07:32,678
Wait a minute,
fellas.

1056
01:07:32,761 --> 01:07:35,681
If he can pay you,
I'll pay you double.

1057
01:07:35,764 --> 01:07:38,642
He already paid us
double.

1058
01:07:39,309 --> 01:07:40,811
Charley?

1059
01:07:44,356 --> 01:07:45,983
Aaah!

1060
01:07:47,985 --> 01:07:49,319
Aaah!

1061
01:07:58,453 --> 01:08:01,707
Daddy,
don't kill him.

1062
01:08:01,790 --> 01:08:06,170
Maybe he'll change
his mind again.

1063
01:08:06,253 --> 01:08:09,923
What the hell did he see
in you in the first place?

1064
01:08:12,009 --> 01:08:14,469
Where are we goin',
fellas?

1065
01:08:35,949 --> 01:08:38,035
Charley, Charley!

1066
01:08:40,078 --> 01:08:42,915
Charley?
Charley?

1067
01:08:45,918 --> 01:08:49,630
I'm sorry about
the honeymoon, Vicki.

1068
01:08:51,465 --> 01:08:53,383
Huh?

1069
01:08:53,467 --> 01:08:58,138
I said, "I'm sorry
about the honeymoon."

1070
01:08:58,222 --> 01:09:00,682
Oh, that's okay,
honey.

1071
01:09:00,766 --> 01:09:04,144
This is the second time
you haven't had one.

1072
01:09:04,228 --> 01:09:06,897
What did you say?
I can't hear you.

1073
01:09:06,980 --> 01:09:11,652
- Excuse me.
- Oh! Oh, they're beautiful.

1074
01:09:13,403 --> 01:09:15,364
What is this?

1075
01:09:15,447 --> 01:09:18,825
Flowers from the
Culver City Boys' Orphanage.

1076
01:09:18,909 --> 01:09:21,453
Oh, Jesus.

1077
01:09:26,291 --> 01:09:28,585
Tomorrow morning
at 8:00...

1078
01:09:28,627 --> 01:09:30,712
I start to take
swimming lessons.

1079
01:09:30,796 --> 01:09:34,258
I lose Esther Williams at the end
of the picture, but what the hell?

1080
01:09:34,341 --> 01:09:36,343
Original score
by Frank Loesser...

1081
01:09:36,426 --> 01:09:39,888
- additional songs by Sammy Fine.
- That's great, Sam.

1082
01:09:39,972 --> 01:09:42,099
- It gets greater.
- Me...

1083
01:09:42,182 --> 01:09:44,977
Fred Astaire
and Rita Hayworth in one picture.

1084
01:09:45,060 --> 01:09:48,230
- Co-Starring?
- Better, I play a funny taxi driver.

1085
01:09:48,313 --> 01:09:50,274
I got one dynamite scene...

1086
01:09:50,315 --> 01:09:53,110
and let Fred and Rita
carry the heavy plot. I'm no dope.

1087
01:09:53,193 --> 01:09:55,320
- Terrific, fellas.
- Let's not forget George.

1088
01:09:55,404 --> 01:09:57,906
Cincinnati's won
four games in a row!

1089
01:09:57,990 --> 01:10:00,951
And Charley's got Vicki.
Everyone finishes in the money!

1090
01:10:00,993 --> 01:10:03,871
I gotta call Vicki.
She had an audition at Paramount.

1091
01:10:03,954 --> 01:10:05,956
I wanna see
how she made out.

1092
01:10:06,039 --> 01:10:10,377
I could tell him.
Nobody's hiring wives of Charley Pearl.

1093
01:10:10,460 --> 01:10:13,422
The irony is,
if he'd married Adele...

1094
01:10:13,505 --> 01:10:16,633
- Vicki would be working today.
- Tell him.

1095
01:10:16,717 --> 01:10:19,219
He loves stories
about irony.

1096
01:10:31,190 --> 01:10:33,150
[Vicki]
Charley?

1097
01:10:33,192 --> 01:10:37,196
Charley,
guess what?

1098
01:10:38,906 --> 01:10:42,242
They want to test me
at Monogram Pictures.

1099
01:10:42,326 --> 01:10:44,494
It's not a
werewolf picture.

1100
01:10:44,578 --> 01:10:47,623
It's a really big
musical!

1101
01:10:47,706 --> 01:10:49,791
Oh, oh!

1102
01:10:49,875 --> 01:10:51,960
I've got to learn
two songs by Wednesday.

1103
01:10:52,044 --> 01:10:54,505
I've got to take some
really fast dancing lessons.

1104
01:10:54,546 --> 01:10:58,175
Charley, if I could just
show them what I can do.

1105
01:10:59,009 --> 01:11:02,054
What's wrong?

1106
01:11:02,137 --> 01:11:05,599
I'm leaving for Boston
in two hours.

1107
01:11:05,682 --> 01:11:08,101
My father
had a stroke.

1108
01:11:08,185 --> 01:11:11,355
They don't think he's
gonna last out the week.

1109
01:11:13,023 --> 01:11:15,400
Charley.

1110
01:11:15,484 --> 01:11:18,403
Oh, honey,
I'm sorry.

1111
01:11:18,487 --> 01:11:22,115
I never thought
about him dying.

1112
01:11:22,199 --> 01:11:25,869
He didn't seem the type,
you know what I mean?

1113
01:11:27,496 --> 01:11:29,998
Did you talk to him?

1114
01:11:30,082 --> 01:11:32,793
No, not really.
He's on oxygen.

1115
01:11:32,876 --> 01:11:35,128
Just a couple
of words.

1116
01:11:35,212 --> 01:11:38,257
What did he say?

1117
01:11:38,340 --> 01:11:41,260
He said he wants
to meet you!

1118
01:11:41,343 --> 01:11:46,265
He said he's not going anywhere
'til he meets his daughter.

1119
01:11:46,348 --> 01:11:50,811
Even after everything
he's read about me?

1120
01:11:50,894 --> 01:11:53,397
Especially.

1121
01:11:53,480 --> 01:11:57,150
I'll tell him
that you wanted to go.

1122
01:11:57,234 --> 01:11:59,695
I'm going with you.

1123
01:11:59,778 --> 01:12:02,072
I'll start packing.

1124
01:12:02,114 --> 01:12:05,450
I'll call Monogram.
They'll postpone the test.

1125
01:12:05,534 --> 01:12:07,452
No, it doesn't matter.

1126
01:12:07,536 --> 01:12:10,664
There were ten other girls.
It was a long shot anyway.

1127
01:12:10,747 --> 01:12:13,166
I'll make it up to you.
I swear.

1128
01:12:13,250 --> 01:12:17,296
Hey, I'm just glad
he wants to meet me.

1129
01:12:17,379 --> 01:12:20,424
[Phil]
When they got to Boston...

1130
01:12:20,507 --> 01:12:22,759
Charley's father
was in a coma.

1131
01:12:22,843 --> 01:12:26,346
Well, they watched and waited...

1132
01:12:26,430 --> 01:12:28,932
and waited and watched
for five solid days...

1133
01:12:29,016 --> 01:12:31,977
just for the old man
to meet Vicki.

1134
01:12:33,437 --> 01:12:37,399
Honey, is it okay
if I go to the bathroom?

1135
01:12:37,482 --> 01:12:39,443
Yeah, sure.

1136
01:12:43,155 --> 01:12:45,324
I'll be right back.

1137
01:13:07,763 --> 01:13:10,974
Where... is she?

1138
01:13:11,058 --> 01:13:14,353
- Where is she!
- Vicki!

1139
01:13:14,436 --> 01:13:17,648
- Where is she?
- Vicki, hurry up!

1140
01:13:19,274 --> 01:13:21,485
[Vicki]
What?

1141
01:13:23,737 --> 01:13:25,656
What?

1142
01:13:26,740 --> 01:13:29,993
You missed him.

1143
01:13:30,035 --> 01:13:32,412
[Phil]
So Charley lost his father...

1144
01:13:32,496 --> 01:13:34,831
and Vicki lost the part
at Monogram.

1145
01:13:34,873 --> 01:13:37,960
The girl who got it?
Bugsy Siegel's new girl...

1146
01:13:38,043 --> 01:13:40,087
the one he dumped
Vicki for.

1147
01:13:40,170 --> 01:13:44,424
You know the odds on that?
You couldn't place the bet.!

1148
01:13:44,508 --> 01:13:49,137
- I'm real sorry he
never got to meet you.
- Yeah.

1149
01:13:49,179 --> 01:13:51,515
He had a
real nice face...

1150
01:13:51,557 --> 01:13:55,477
so... gentle.

1151
01:13:57,187 --> 01:14:00,315
Well, he
was in a coma.

1152
01:14:01,775 --> 01:14:04,444
When are
we going home?

1153
01:14:04,528 --> 01:14:07,990
I've got some business
to take care of.

1154
01:14:08,031 --> 01:14:10,868
I am the president
of the company now.

1155
01:14:10,951 --> 01:14:13,203
When can we leave?

1156
01:14:13,245 --> 01:14:17,666
I don't know.
I'd say in about two years.

1157
01:14:24,214 --> 01:14:28,343
After that, we'd only have to spend
seven or eight months a year here.

1158
01:14:31,555 --> 01:14:34,016
Two years?

1159
01:14:34,099 --> 01:14:36,560
Honey, the company
isn't doing well.

1160
01:14:36,643 --> 01:14:40,063
If I don't go to work,
we could lose everything.

1161
01:14:42,065 --> 01:14:43,984
Two years!

1162
01:14:44,067 --> 01:14:47,029
You've got to give me
at least a year and a half.

1163
01:14:47,070 --> 01:14:51,033
If a picture comes up,
you go to L.A. And do it.

1164
01:14:51,116 --> 01:14:53,076
Pictures don't
come up in Boston.

1165
01:14:53,160 --> 01:14:55,913
You don't get to do
screen tests in Massachusetts...

1166
01:14:55,996 --> 01:14:58,332
or meet directors or producers
on Plymouth Rock!

1167
01:14:58,415 --> 01:15:02,753
I had a hard enough time getting into
the studios when I was there every day.

1168
01:15:02,794 --> 01:15:05,714
- Why was that, Charley?
- It's a tough business.

1169
01:15:05,756 --> 01:15:10,260
Especially when you're married
to the guy who dumped Adele Horner.

1170
01:15:10,344 --> 01:15:13,096
Right.
And who did I dump her for?

1171
01:15:13,138 --> 01:15:15,891
Isn't that worth
two years of your life?

1172
01:15:15,933 --> 01:15:19,061
Is it a torture to live
in a place like this?

1173
01:15:19,102 --> 01:15:22,231
This is high society.
It doesn't get any higher.

1174
01:15:22,272 --> 01:15:25,400
I just want a chance
to do it on my own.

1175
01:15:25,442 --> 01:15:27,444
I can understand that.

1176
01:15:27,486 --> 01:15:30,280
All I want is
what's coming to me.

1177
01:15:30,322 --> 01:15:32,741
- Don't touch me.
- You're good at singing.

1178
01:15:32,783 --> 01:15:36,411
I'm very good at
inheriting money.

1179
01:15:36,495 --> 01:15:39,456
I may be the best
in my field.

1180
01:15:39,498 --> 01:15:44,127
I just don't want
to be without you.

1181
01:15:46,213 --> 01:15:50,259
I'll leave it up to you.
Whatever you decide is fine.

1182
01:15:52,970 --> 01:15:56,431
You know I can't be
without you two years.

1183
01:15:56,515 --> 01:15:59,268
Oh, God!

1184
01:15:59,309 --> 01:16:01,937
[Phil]
So they stayed...

1185
01:16:01,979 --> 01:16:05,774
and Vicki began the pleasant
process of fitting into Boston.

1186
01:16:05,816 --> 01:16:09,069
A lot of parties, new clothes,
a lot ofhats.

1187
01:16:09,152 --> 01:16:11,405
I recall she mentioned hats.

1188
01:16:11,488 --> 01:16:16,243
Meanwhile, Charley became obsessed
with saving the family business.

1189
01:16:16,326 --> 01:16:19,246
He was determined
to make the old man proud.

1190
01:16:19,329 --> 01:16:22,082
Vicki spent her nights alone
waiting for Charley.

1191
01:16:22,165 --> 01:16:24,084
He was very busy.

1192
01:16:24,168 --> 01:16:27,754
He was making major
important business decisions.

1193
01:16:27,838 --> 01:16:31,592
It needs a little more mint, guys.

1194
01:16:34,887 --> 01:16:38,473
Vicki, darling,
how long have you been here?

1195
01:16:40,350 --> 01:16:42,978
Vicki, darling?

1196
01:16:45,189 --> 01:16:49,193
Oh, ah, two years.
We've been here two years.

1197
01:16:49,276 --> 01:16:51,945
Carl and I were
married two years...

1198
01:16:52,029 --> 01:16:53,947
when our
sex life died.

1199
01:16:54,031 --> 01:16:56,700
We had a small funeral.
It was lovely.

1200
01:16:56,783 --> 01:17:01,288
- Charles is having an affair
with his secretary.
- What?

1201
01:17:01,371 --> 01:17:02,998
Oh, no, no,
darling.

1202
01:17:03,040 --> 01:17:06,502
My Charles,
not your Charles.

1203
01:17:06,543 --> 01:17:10,380
Oh!
I didn't think...

1204
01:17:10,422 --> 01:17:14,009
Everything is all right
with you two, isn't it?

1205
01:17:14,051 --> 01:17:17,471
Oh, absolutely.
We're fine.

1206
01:17:17,554 --> 01:17:20,557
He's just
a little busy.

1207
01:17:20,641 --> 01:17:24,853
- Busy?
- "Just have to finish
these reports, dear."

1208
01:17:31,735 --> 01:17:34,154
- Hi.
- Hi.

1209
01:17:34,238 --> 01:17:36,698
Whatcha doing?

1210
01:17:36,782 --> 01:17:39,493
I gotta get through
these reports.

1211
01:17:39,576 --> 01:17:42,204
How much longer?

1212
01:17:42,246 --> 01:17:44,248
Couple of hours.

1213
01:17:44,289 --> 01:17:46,416
Oh, Charley!

1214
01:17:46,500 --> 01:17:49,920
I miss you so much.

