- Give me that.
- Five guys in one room?

1446
01:32:31,051 --> 01:32:34,471
In the minor leagues,
the whole team sleeps in one room.

1447
01:32:34,555 --> 01:32:36,765
I get a bed.

1448
01:33:03,667 --> 01:33:05,627
Where were you?

1449
01:33:07,004 --> 01:33:09,756
I'm freezing.
Close the window.

1450
01:33:15,387 --> 01:33:17,472
Oh, Vicki, baby.

1451
01:33:17,556 --> 01:33:20,809
- I missed you so much.
- Stop right there.

1452
01:33:23,729 --> 01:33:28,317
Is it back?
That old feeling...

1453
01:33:28,400 --> 01:33:32,446
that you'd go nuts
if you don't get to touch me?

1454
01:33:33,530 --> 01:33:35,490
Yeah, it's back.

1455
01:33:35,532 --> 01:33:37,701
We have to talk first.

1456
01:33:37,784 --> 01:33:40,204
Stand over there.

1457
01:33:43,790 --> 01:33:47,294
What's changed, Charley?
I still want to be a singer.

1458
01:33:47,377 --> 01:33:50,172
You still want to be
chairman of the board.

1459
01:33:50,214 --> 01:33:52,508
Somebody's got
to give up something.

1460
01:33:53,717 --> 01:33:56,303
I gave up
my stock options.

1461
01:33:56,386 --> 01:33:58,889
I sold my house.

1462
01:33:58,972 --> 01:34:02,518
I left all that
behind.

1463
01:34:04,811 --> 01:34:07,231
I went crazy
without you, baby.

1464
01:34:10,567 --> 01:34:13,987
I took that job
in Vegas...

1465
01:34:14,071 --> 01:34:18,867
'cause I knew it was
the one place that you'd find me.

1466
01:34:18,909 --> 01:34:21,036
I never would've
stopped looking.

1467
01:34:21,078 --> 01:34:24,248
Charley, this is a curse.

1468
01:34:24,331 --> 01:34:27,584
It's okay to love somebody...

1469
01:34:27,668 --> 01:34:32,840
but it's neurotic to think
you can't live without them.

1470
01:34:32,923 --> 01:34:34,883
I read that
in "Reader's Digest."

1471
01:34:34,925 --> 01:34:36,844
I want you back.

1472
01:34:36,927 --> 01:34:39,596
We'll live in L.A.
You can sing, dance, act...

1473
01:34:39,680 --> 01:34:42,516
Whatever the hell you want,
so long as we're together.

1474
01:34:42,599 --> 01:34:44,518
Please?

1475
01:34:44,601 --> 01:34:47,187
You won't regret it.

1476
01:34:47,271 --> 01:34:49,523
I promise, Charley.

1477
01:34:49,606 --> 01:34:51,733
Look at you.

1478
01:34:51,817 --> 01:34:54,069
Let's get married
in the morning, baby.

1479
01:34:54,111 --> 01:34:56,196
Ah, shit, Charley!

1480
01:34:56,280 --> 01:35:00,200
- I don't want to get married again.
- We've rehearsed twice.

1481
01:35:00,284 --> 01:35:03,203
We're practically professionals.
What's the problem?

1482
01:35:03,287 --> 01:35:05,789
- Do you, Charles Raymond Pearl...
- I do.

1483
01:35:05,873 --> 01:35:09,459
- Take Victoria to be your
lawfully wedded wife?
- I do.

1484
01:35:09,543 --> 01:35:12,963
Not yet.
For as long as you both shall live?

1485
01:35:13,005 --> 01:35:15,215
- Now.
- I do.

1486
01:35:15,299 --> 01:35:18,385
If the man says, "Can do,"
can do.

1487
01:35:18,468 --> 01:35:20,888
Do you,
Victoria Rosemary Anderson...

1488
01:35:20,971 --> 01:35:22,639
