1631
01:43:56,820 --> 01:43:58,947
You come back here.

1632
01:43:59,031 --> 01:44:02,117
Where do you think
you're going?

1633
01:44:02,201 --> 01:44:05,537
Come back and get in this car.
Do you hear me?

1634
01:44:05,621 --> 01:44:09,791
Come back, goddamn it.
You owe me the rest of your life!

1635
01:44:09,833 --> 01:44:11,877
What about my kids?

1636
01:44:11,960 --> 01:44:14,505
I'm not giving up
my kids!

1637
01:44:14,588 --> 01:44:17,799
I don't want my kids to have
a revolving door as a father.

1638
01:44:17,883 --> 01:44:21,678
We have more anniversaries
than we do birthdays!

1639
01:44:21,762 --> 01:44:24,848
I'm a great father.
I love being a father.

1640
01:44:24,932 --> 01:44:28,393
Too bad you don't love
being a husband!

1641
01:44:28,477 --> 01:44:30,729
Look at me, Charley.
Look at me!

1642
01:44:30,812 --> 01:44:34,399
'Cause it's the last chance
you're ever gonna get.

1643
01:44:56,505 --> 01:44:59,424
Goddamn you,
Bugsy Siegel.

1644
01:45:00,801 --> 01:45:03,345
I hope you burn
in hell.

1645
